{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μέλισσᾰ</b>, <br /> <i>Attic dialect</i> <b>μέλιττα</b>, ης, ἡ, (perhaps by haplology for μελι-λιχ-yα 'honey-licker', cf. Sanskrit <i>madhu-lih-</i> (corresp. with Gr. Μεθυ-λιχ-) 'bee') <b>bee</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.106, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>wild bees</b>, that live in rocks, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.87, compare 12.167 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of <b>honey-bees</b>, that live in hives, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 594; σμῆνος μελισσᾶν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 128 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.194, 5.10:—Phrases: ὥσπερ μέλιττα τὸ κέντρον ἐγκαταλιπών 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 91c \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὄνος ἐν μελίτταις 'a hornets' nest', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Crates Comicus 36; compare μέλι 1.2 near the end \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> the term μέλισσα was applied <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> to <b>poets</b>, from their culling the beauties of nature, ἔνθεν ὡσπερεὶ μ. Φρύνιχος.. μελέων ἀπεβόσκετο καρπόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 748; μ. Μούσης [prev. author] “Ec.” 974 (Lyric poetry); μ. Ἤρινναν Μουσῶν ἄνθεα δρεπτομέναν “Anthologia Graeca” 7.13 (1st c.AD: Leonidas Alexandrinus Epigrammaticus or 1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of Sophocles, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 460. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> to the <b>priestesses</b> of Delphi, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.60 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Demeter and Artemis, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus [same place], 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Antro Nympharum - Porphyrii Opuscula” 18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Cybele, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Didymus Grammaticus cited in Lact. “Inst.” 1.22. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> in Neo-Platonic Philos., <b>any pure, chaste being</b>, of souls coming to birth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Antro Nympharum - Porphyrii Opuscula” 19 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; of the Moon,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 18. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ={μέλι}, <b>honey</b>, ὕδατος, μελίσσης, μηδὲ προσφέρειν μέθυ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 481: _metaphorically_, γλώσσης μελίσσῃ καταρρυηκέναι [prev. author] “fragment” 155 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of poetry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 9.505.6\">Refs</a>]; ἑσμὸς μελίσσης appears to be corrupt in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Epinicus Comicus 1.7. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> ={ὀβολός}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8283","accentedUnicode":"μέλισσα","shortDef":"bee","mediumDef":"bee","stepGloss":"bee","stepTransliteration":"melissa","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}